# API Architecture Standard

## Purpose

This rule defines the API layer standards for the enterprise e-commerce platform.

The API is the contract between backend business capabilities and the Next.js frontend (and future consumers). Every endpoint must be secure, predictable, documented, and versioned.

---

# Scope

Applies to all code under `apps/api/`.

Covers:

- FastAPI application structure
- REST resource design
- Request/response models
- Error handling
- Integration with domain/application layers
- Consumer expectations for Next.js

Does not define frontend fetch patterns in depth — see `frontend/00-frontend`.

---

# Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Framework | FastAPI |
| Validation | Pydantic v2 |
| ORM | SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async) |
| Auth | JWT / session cookies (see `api/04-auth-api`) |
| Documentation | OpenAPI 3.1 auto-generated + curated |
| ASGI server | Uvicorn / Gunicorn |

---

# Architectural Position

The API is the Presentation layer in Clean Architecture.

```
HTTP Request
    ↓
Router (FastAPI)
    ↓
Dependencies (auth, db session)
    ↓
Application Service (use case)
    ↓
Domain
    ↓
Infrastructure (repository)
    ↓
HTTP Response
```

Routers never contain business logic.

Routers never access repositories directly.

